summary: SPLATOON 2'S FINAL SPLATFEST IS 'CHAOS VS. ORDER,' COMING JULY 18TH, 2019, VERSION 5.0 UPDATE TO FEATURE TURF WAR SPLATFEST MODE
title: SPLATOON 2'S FINAL SPLATFEST IS 'CHAOS VS. ORDER,' COMING JULY 18TH, 2019, VERSION 5.0 UPDATE TO FEATURE TURF WAR SPLATFEST MODE
body:
Nintendo has announced the final Splatfest for Splatoon 2, which is taking place on July 18th to 21st, 2019. The theme will be Chaos Vs. Order, and some special goodies are coming for this event. There will be a new Shifty Station layout, as well as an appearance from all previous Shifty Station stages.

There will also be some new gear available via the Splatfest, which you can see in the image above.

Finally, Nintendo announced that the Version 5.0 update is going to come after the final Splatfest takes place. One aspect detailed for that update was the Turf War Splatfest, which will let players revisit all 24 Shifty Station designs, and that includes both the day and night options.

 Nintendo have announced a fifth Splatoon Koshien tournament beginning this October in...
body:
Splatoon Koshien Returns This Year

Nintendo have announced a fifth Splatoon Koshien tournament beginning this October in five cities (Hokkaido, Tokyo, Nagoya, Kyoto, and Fukuoka) across Japan, with two days at each venue and 1.5 times the number of participants, making this the biggest Splatoon Koshien tournament to date!
